    <section id="postingbody">
        <div class="print-information print-qrcode-container">
            <p class="print-qrcode-label">QR Code Link to This Post</p>
            <div class="print-qrcode" data-location="http://chicago.craigslist.org/wcl/fbh/6042100549.html"></div>
        </div>
Hotel Arista is not a chain, rather, we're something a little different. We're an independent, locally owned boutique hotel and something of a maverick. We offer effortless and luxurious accommodations for business, leisure and weddings.<br>
<br>
Our guests are people who like to write their own story -- leaders, innovators, high-profile couples, chic brides, authors, actors, film crews and more. This is a crowd that likes the seduction of an effortless, evocative experience and the glamour of making a place their own. Personal taste and choice are considered paramount at Hotel Arista, and guests select from an extensive personal preference menu of amenities and services.<br>
<br>
Hotel Arista at CityGate Centre in Naperville is a four-diamond award winner and the first LEED certified hotel in Illinois.<br>
<br>
Our Dishwashers (Stewards) maintain an immaculate and efficient kitchen by: cleaning all dishware, china, crystal and silver, pots and pans, and stocking cleaning products, emptying trash bins and replacing garbage bags, assists in "break down" and cleanliness of buffets.<br>
<br>
Responsibilities:<br>
<br>
-Collects dirty pans from the cooking line and transport to pot station for cleaning.<br>
-Cleans and maintains sanitation areas and organize cleaning supplies including hanging up mops and brooms.<br>
-Ensures clean items are stored appropriately.<br>
-Operates and maintains cleaning equipment and tools, including the dish washing machine, hand wash stations pot-scrubbing station, and trash compactor.<br>
-Ensures that all spills and breakage are attended to immediately.<br>
-Follows hotel and departmental policies and procedures including safe practices in the workplace.<br>
-Be familiar with applicable emergency procedures and evacuations including fire, bomb threat, power failure, and injury to and illness of persons.<br>
-Must have a flexible schedule and be available to work nights weekends, and holidays.<br>
-Completes any other tasks as assigned by your manager.<br>
<br>
QualificationsEducation<br>
-High school diploma or equivalent education<br>
<br>
Experience<br>
-Familiarity with proper sanitation regulations.<br>
<br>
Skills<br>
-Excellent written and verbal skills.<br>
-Neat and clean appearance<br>
-Ability to work in a team environment.<br>
<br>
Physical Requirements<br>
-Must be able to walk and stand for up to 8 hours a day, with or without reasonable accommodation.<br>
-Reach overhead and below the knees, including bending, twisting, pulling, and stooping.<br>
-Must be able to bend, squat and lift up to 50 lbs. on a regular and continuing basis.<br>
<br>
To take a closer look, simply log onto: www.hotelarista.com<br>
<br>
To apply, please select the following link:<br>
<br>
<a href="https://www.paycomonline.net/v4/ats/index.php?/job/apply&clientkey=DBC1C3C782DBBBC7C7E0A4171B8A29DD&job=29045&jpt=15908f0294bf5f20231f1d75f1fa2bbb" rel="nofollow">https://www.paycomonline.net/v4/ats/index.php?/job/apply&clientkey=DBC1C3C782DBBBC7C7E0A4171B8A29DD&job=29045&jpt=15908f0294bf5f20231f1d75f1fa2bbb</a><br>
<br>
We are an equal opportunity employer and make employment decisions without regard to age, race, religion, national origin, gender, disability, veteran status, genetic information, sexual orientation and gender identity or any other protected class. Our locations are drug-free and pre-employment drug tests are required. Background checks are also required before employment begins. We participate in E-Verify and those who are ineligible to work in the United States will not be considered.<br>
